WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:01.753
- <i>Previously on</i> The Originals...
- And Marcel,

00:01.755 --> 00:03.710
no one's seen him in over 24 hours.

00:03.711 --> 00:06.146
Because he's locked in a dungeon.

00:07.850 --> 00:09.683
You're the high priest of the Hollow.

00:09.685 --> 00:11.802
You're the one who allowed
the Hollow into this world.

00:11.804 --> 00:14.390
See, your ancestors were the
only thing holding him back

00:14.393 --> 00:15.992
and when you severed that link

00:15.995 --> 00:17.324
you allowed it to go free.

00:17.326 --> 00:19.292
[crowd gasps, mutters]

00:22.130 --> 00:23.797
What Elijah did...

00:23.799 --> 00:25.098
Hey, in my family it's

00:25.100 --> 00:27.033
lots of fighting, lots of violence,

00:27.035 --> 00:29.102
so that's why I chose a different path.

00:29.104 --> 00:30.103
Made my own life.

00:30.105 --> 00:31.859
So can you, you know.

00:31.862 --> 00:33.306
The Hollow has been haunting

00:33.308 --> 00:34.674
the city for a very long time

00:34.676 --> 00:36.042
and when it does bubble up

00:36.044 --> 00:38.044
it always does so in a pattern of four.

00:38.046 --> 00:39.613
It's looking for something.

00:39.615 --> 00:41.982
And I'm pretty sure
that I have one of them.

00:41.984 --> 00:43.517
When a witch wishes to be reborn,

00:43.519 --> 00:45.744
its remains are required
to complete the spell.

00:45.747 --> 00:47.047
Who has the other three?

00:47.050 --> 00:48.315
Dominic said that

00:48.318 --> 00:49.990
he had found something here.

00:49.992 --> 00:52.425
[chanting in foreign language]

00:52.427 --> 00:55.228
[gasps]

00:55.230 --> 00:56.763
KLAUS: <i>The Tunde Blade...</i>

00:56.765 --> 00:59.332
<i>it's gone.</i>

01:05.007 --> 01:07.140
Ugh, O-positive.

01:07.142 --> 01:08.341
You heathen.

01:08.343 --> 01:09.309
New rules.

01:09.311 --> 01:10.634
No blood shed in the house

01:10.637 --> 01:13.780
where my daughter sleeps and plays.

01:13.782 --> 01:15.048
Perhaps I'll go out for dinner.

01:15.050 --> 01:16.047
Oh, no, no, no, no.

01:16.050 --> 01:18.428
We have no way to know who
will take Dominic's place

01:18.431 --> 01:19.639
as the Hollow's right hand.

01:19.642 --> 01:21.321
There could be any number
of disciples out there.

01:21.323 --> 01:24.426
Yes, yes, yes, all who may
have the means to kill us.

01:24.429 --> 01:26.993
You know, if you hadn't
been so hasty to kill him,

01:26.995 --> 01:28.762
we'd be dealing with the devil we know.

01:28.764 --> 01:31.364
Spoken by the devil I know best of all.

01:31.366 --> 01:32.891
I take it you have a plan.

01:34.736 --> 01:36.836
Freya will place a barrier
spell on the compound.

01:36.838 --> 01:38.171
No one gets in or out.

01:38.173 --> 01:41.007
Oh, so we're to stay here

01:41.009 --> 01:43.743
while our enemies seek to
resurrect this monstrosity

01:43.745 --> 01:45.345
and let me guess,

01:45.347 --> 01:47.414
you won't be confined here.

01:47.416 --> 01:48.748
I have a little errand to run.

01:48.750 --> 01:51.051
And while you're off
cavorting all over town,

01:51.053 --> 01:52.552
I'm what?

01:52.554 --> 01:53.753
Grounded?

01:53.755 --> 01:55.956
Essentially.

01:57.092 --> 01:58.758
Why don't you take out your frustration

01:58.760 --> 02:01.962
on that filthy jawbone our
enemy seems so fascinated by.

02:01.964 --> 02:04.731
Gladly.

02:04.733 --> 02:07.434
♪ ♪

02:10.606 --> 02:13.607
[indistinct chatter]

02:17.846 --> 02:21.233
HOPE: <i>"A man of words and not of deeds,</i>

02:21.236 --> 02:22.616
<i>is like a garden</i>

02:22.618 --> 02:24.684
<i>full of weeds."</i>

02:28.190 --> 02:30.557
"And when the weeds begin to crawl,

02:30.559 --> 02:33.526
it's like a bird upon the wall."

02:36.031 --> 02:37.998
<i>"And when the bird away</i>

02:38.000 --> 02:40.015
<i>does fly, it's like an eagle</i>

02:40.018 --> 02:42.002
<i>in the sky."</i>

02:42.004 --> 02:43.436
[chuckles]

02:43.438 --> 02:46.439
<i>"And when the sky begins to roar,</i>

02:46.441 --> 02:49.309
<i>it's like a lion at the door."</i>

02:51.446 --> 02:53.926
<i>"And when the door begins to crack..."</i>

02:54.983 --> 02:58.151
<i>"...it's like a stick across your back."</i>

02:58.153 --> 02:59.653
[shouts]

03:00.822 --> 03:03.923
<i>"And when your back begins to smart,</i>

03:03.925 --> 03:06.860
<i>it's like a knife inside your heart.</i>

03:06.862 --> 03:09.863
And when your heart begins to bleed,

03:09.865 --> 03:13.900
you're dead and dead and dead indeed."

03:13.902 --> 03:15.468
Not exactly the most

03:15.470 --> 03:16.970
uplifting reading material.

03:18.473 --> 03:19.706
It's an old book of rhymes.

03:19.708 --> 03:21.527
There's a lot of weird stuff here.

03:21.530 --> 03:22.742
You know, Hope,

03:22.744 --> 03:24.678
I'd rather you didn't
play here, actually.

03:24.680 --> 03:26.980
All the splinters and the dust...

03:30.152 --> 03:31.384
and the bats.

03:31.386 --> 03:34.287
There aren't any bats.

03:34.289 --> 03:36.423
I've seen no evidence
that your Uncle Elijah

03:36.425 --> 03:38.758
doesn't sleep here, hanging upside down.

03:39.828 --> 03:41.428
Dad...

03:41.431 --> 03:43.898
was there a little boy
who used to live here?

03:45.000 --> 03:51.074
